Defendant Corey Lavell Anderson in court with attorney Gabriel William Houghton.  Defendant Corey Lavell Anderson in custody.  Jesica Ballenger appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

Defendant prepared to enter change of plea.  Hearing proceeded.  Negotiations set forth by the state.

The defendant was advised of his constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Addendum to Plea Questionnaire, and Jury Instructions received and filed.  The parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  The Court found the defendant guilty and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.  Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes Section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession and Voting.  Filed, Ineligible Voting Notice and Acknowledgement.    

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by State, defense, and defendant. 
 
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 55 MONTHS, CONSECUTIVE to any other time being served with credit for 0 days served. The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 15 MONTHS.  The MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION IS 40 MONTHS.

The defendant IS NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Substance Abuse Program.

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
*Cooperate with any and all rules set forth by the probation agent;
*No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause;
*No contact with Wells Fargo Bank;
*Obtain/maintain full time employment or full time school and part time employment;
*Participate in vocational training/job skills program if available;
*Participate in Cognitive Thinking program;
*Pay all supervision fees;
*Provide DNA sample- surcharge WAIVED due to large amount of restitution ordered;

The court orders all remaining surcharges, fees, assessments, and costs WAIVED due to large amount of restitution ordered by the court.  State in compliance with victim rights legislation.  The Court ordered restitution in the stipulated amount of $11,474.34 payable to Wells Fargo Bank.  The Court ordered that all financial obligations and restitution be paid through collection of sums by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment.  Appeal rights given by the court.
